{
  "Function Notation": "",
  "This lesson covers the fundamental measures of center used to analyze and summarize data sets. You'll learn how to calculate and apply the mean, median, and mode, and understand when each is most appropriate.": "",
  "If f(x) = 3x + 1, what is f(4)?": "",
  "f(4) = 3(4) + 1 = 12 + 1 = 13.": "",
  "If g(x) = x^2 - 5, what is g(3)?": "",
  "g(3) = 3^2 - 5 = 9 - 5 = 4.": "",
  "If h(x) = -2x + 10, what is h(-3)?": "",
  "h(-3) = -2(-3) + 10 = 6 + 10 = 16.": "",
  "If f(x) = 4x and g(x) = x + 3, what is f(g(2))?": "",
  "First find g(2) = 2 + 3 = 5. Then f(5) = 4(5) = 20.": "",
  "If f(x) = x^2 + 2x, what is f(0)?": "",
  "f(0) = 0^2 + 2(0) = 0 + 0 = 0.": "",
  "If p(t) = -16t^2 + 64, what is p(1)?": "",
  "p(1) = -16(1)^2 + 64 = -16 + 64 = 48.": "",
  "If f(x) = 2x + 7, what is f(a + 1)?": "",
  "f(a + 1) = 2(a + 1) + 7 = 2a + 2 + 7 = 2a + 9.": "",
  "If f(x) = |x - 4|, what is f(1)?": "",
  "f(1) = |1 - 4| = |-3| = 3.": "",
